<TITLE>Aravind Srinivasan's Biography</TITLE>

<BODY BGCOLOR = "#ffffff" TEXT="green" LINK="#856363" VLINK="#238E68">

<A HREF="http://www.cs.umd.edu/~srin">Aravind Srinivasan</A> (born 1968) is
a <a href = "https://cmns.umd.edu/news-events/features/4617">Distinguished University Professor</a> and 
a Professor with the Department of Computer
Science and the Institute for Advanced Computer Studies 
at the University of Maryland, College Park. He received
his undergraduate degree from the Indian Institute of Technology, 
Madras, and his Ph.D. from Cornell University, both in Computer 
Science. He was a postdoctoral researcher at the
Institute for Advanced Study in Princeton and at DIMACS. 
He has also worked at the National University of Singapore, and in industrial research at Bell Labs. <P>

Aravind Srinivasan's main research-interests are in algorithms, probabilistic
methods, data science, network science, and machine learning: theory, and applications in areas including health, E-commerce, cloud computing, Internet advertising, and fairness. They span areas including: 
<ul>
  <li> Algorithms, probabilistic methods, and continuous/combinatorial optimization; </li>
    <li> Interpretability and explainability in AI; </li> 
<li>The interface of algorithms, AI, and machine learning in: 
<ul>
<li>Data science and health: incl. computational epidemiology, (cancer) genomics, pharmacology, organ exchange, and medical devices. </li>
<li>Data science and the Internet economy: incl. E-commerce, digital marketing, cloud optimization, crowdsourcing, and social networks. </li>
<li>Data science and fairness: systematically incorporating (probabilistic, per-user/demographic) fairness in AI and in algorithms. 
</ul> 
<li> Algorithms in networking (wireless and peer-to-peer), social networks, and
distributed/parallel computing; </li>
<li> Computational approaches to sustainable growth (incl. energy, monitoring
and sensing, electric-power and water networks). </li>
</ul>

He has published more than 150 papers in these areas, 
in fora including <em>Nature</em>, 
<em>Journal of the ACM</em>, <em>IEEE/ACM Transactions on Networking</em>, 
and the <em>SIAM Journal on Computing</em>. 
He is/was an Associate Editor for the 
<a href = "http://talg.acm.org"><em>ACM Transactions on Algorithms</em></a> (<em>Editor-in-Chief</em>, 2014-2020),  
an Editor for
<a href = "http://www.theoryofcomputing.org"><em>Theory of Computing</em></A>
(<em>Managing Editor</em>, 2006-2019; Editor, 2019-2026)  
the 
<a href = "http://journal.library.iisc.ernet.in/index.php/iisc"><em>Journal of the IISc</em></a> and other journals, 
and has served on the 
program committees of various conferences. His papers have been
(co-)recipients of the Best Paper/Best Student Paper/Test of Time Awards at 
various conferences in areas including algorithms, public health, multi-agent 
systems, model-based prediction, networking, and social
networks. 
<P>

Dr. Srinivasan was appointed a <em>Distinguished 
University Professor</em> of the University of Maryland in 2020: this is the 
highest academic honor the university confers upon its faculty. 
He is an elected Fellow of six professional societies: 
<a href = "http://awards.acm.org/fellow/year.cfm">ACM</a>,
<a href = "http://membercentral.aaas.org/fellows">AAAS</a>,  
<a href = "http://www.ieee.org/membership_services/membership/fellows/index.html">IEEE</a>,
<a href = "http://cvs.cs.umd.edu/article/2018/11/professor-aravind-srinivasan-named-ams-fellow-2019">AMS</a>, 
<a href = "http://eatcs.org/index.php/component/content/article/1-news/2426--eatcs-fellows-class-of-2017-named">EATCS</a>, 
and
<a href = "https://sinews.siam.org/Details-Page/siam-announces-class-of-2020-fellows">SIAM</a>. 
He was elected a Member of <a href = "https://ae-info.org"><em>Academia Europaea</em></a>, the Academy of Europe, in 2018. 
He received a 
<a href = "http://alumni.iitm.ac.in/daa/list.php?yr=2016">Distinguished Alumnus Award</a> from his <em>alma mater</em> 
<a href = "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Institute_of_Technology_Madras">IIT Madras</a>. He also received the 
<a href = "http://www.umiacs.umd.edu/about-us/news/srinivasan-receives-cmns-board-visitors-distinguished-faculty-award">Distinguished Faculty Award</a> from the Board of
Visitors of the 
College of Computing, Mathematical, and Natural Sciences (University
of Maryland) in 2016. 
He is a recipient of the <a href = "https://www.podc.org/dijkstra">Dijkstra Prize</a>, the <a href = "https://www.sigact.org/prizes/student.html">Danny Lewin Award</a>, and the <em>Distinguished Career Award in Computer Science</em> from the Washington Academy of Sciences.
One of his coauthored papers on forecasting/prediction received a KDD <em>Test of Time Award</em> in 2025.
His past and current research have been funded by
research awards from Adobe, Amazon, and Google, and by grants/contracts from 
the NSF, IARPA, the Laboratory for Telecommunication Sciences, and USARO.
He received a <em>Thought Leader Award</em> from the IIT Madras Alumni Association in 2025. 
He was eighth in India in the Joint Entrance Examination for the Indian
Institutes of Technology (IITs) in 1985. 
<P>

Aravind Srinivasan served as Vice Chair of
the <em>IEEE Technical Committee on the Mathematical Foundations of Computing</em> from 2015 to 2017. He has served on the Board of Advisors for <em>ZeroFOX Inc.</em> and on the Data Science Advisory Board for <em>Janssen Research & Development LLC</em>. 
He has been serving as an <a href = "https://www.amazon.science/working-at-amazon/aravind-srinivasan-amazon-scholar-focuses-on-combinatorial-optimization-algorithms-and-ai">Amazon Scholar</a> since 2019. 
<P>

Aravind's <a href = "https://www.cs.umd.edu/~srin/cvw.pdf">detailed CV</a> 
